turn.2: Lygkos  Lygkos (), also transliterated as "Lyngos" or "Lygos",  is a remote mountain range in the eastern Ioannina and the western Grevena regional unit in northwestern Greece.
turn.3: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.4: It is a part of the Pindus mountain range.
turn.5: Is it a part of something else?
turn.6: Its highest point is the Avgo, at 2,177 m elevation.
turn.7: What else do the mountains do?
turn.8: The Lygkos mountains lie in a horseshoe shape around the Valia Kalda (Βάλια Κάλντα) valley, which exits towards the Aoos valley to the west.
turn.9: Is there anything else notable about it?
turn.10: The Valia Kalda is part of the Pindus-Valia Kalda National Park, founded in 1966.
turn.12: It is one of the coldest and wettest regions of Greece.
